    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-04-21T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-04-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="17"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <head>17. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Iran</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d17fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, DEF 19–3 U.S.-IRAN. Confidential. Drafted by Padelford and Cain in
                        International Logistics Negotiations in <gloss target="#t_DODISA1"
                            >DOD/ISA</gloss>; cleared in substance by <persName corresp="#p_TMG1"
                            >Tiger</persName>, Skiles, and Towsley and in draft by Preble; and
                        approved by <persName corresp="#p_BKW1">Bracken</persName>. Repeated to
                            <gloss target="#t_CINCSTRIKE1">CINCSTRIKE</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_CINCMEAFSA1">CINCMEAFSA</gloss>, and <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCSTRIKE1">CINCSTRIKE</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_CINCMEAFSA1">CINCMEAFSA</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_POLAD1"
                            >POLAD</gloss> Tampa.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-04-21T17:00:00-05:00">April 21, 1964, 5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>785. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 774;<note n="2" xml:id="d17fn2">
                        <ref target="#d16">Document 16</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 922.<note n="3" xml:id="d17fn3">
                        <ref target="#d15">Document 15</ref>.</note> Joint State-<gloss
                        target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>-Defense message. While future plans for Iran
                    not sufficiently finalized to allow making any commitment re credit at this
                    time, there are available several sources of credit for military sales without
                    new Congressional appropriation being required. These sources include the <gloss
                        target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss> reimbursement account (Section 508 of the
                    Foreign Assistance Act) and utilization of Defense stocks (Section 507(a) of the
                        <gloss target="#t_FAA1">FAA</gloss>). Also, the dependable undertaking
                    method of payment (Section 507(b) of the <gloss target="#t_FAA1">FAA</gloss>),
                    while not credit, may be utilized for procurement of materials. In line with
                        <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> policy of gradually shifting <gloss
                        target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss> recipient countries to a reimbursement basis,
                        <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> would be legitimate claimant for credit
                    during period current five-year plan for spare parts, reimbursement items, etc.
                    For deliveries after <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 67, assuming continued
                    rate of balanced economic growth for Iran, we see no reason at present why Iran
                    should not be a legitimate claimant for larger amounts of credit for military
                    purchases. We should keep credit possibilities in mind in reaching our
                    conclusions about a financially feasible modernization program.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
